
eg:

	<link rel="stylesheet" href="file/sample.css" media="max-width:500px;min-height:900px">
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="file/sample.css" media="min-width:300px">




	"@media"

		Syntax:

			@media <screentype> and (dimentions) and (orientation) {
				...
				...
				...
			}


		eg:

			@media screen and (min-width:490px) {
				class1{
					...
				}
				.class2 {
					...
					...
				}
				...
			}

			@media (min-width:400px) and (orientation:landscape) {
				...
				...
				...
			}


Following are different types of screen types can be added

	print - for adding css while print
	screen - to all color screen
	handheld - For smaller screens
	projection - For projecters
	tv - For television
	etc.


Following are different values can be added for orientation type

	1. landscape
	2. potrait


	